http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/School-exhibition/article13998404.ece

Students of Karnataka Public School recreated villages with folk arts and traditional practices in an exhibition on Wednesday. Student dressed in colourful dresses in native styles, and played roles of farmers and home makers.Some wore hand woven clothes and acted as folk artists.They enacted scenes of in front of a village temple, a weekly shandy where the bangle seller gets mobbed by women, the naming ceremony of a child in a family, farmers drying grain, craftsmen making wares, awoman cooking, a vegetable vendor going door to door.